8. The system of claim 1 wherein said mutli-layer structure further comprises
a second layer comprising Cr;
a third layer comprising a CrMoTa alloy;
a fourth layer comprising a CoCrTa alloy;
a fifth layer comprising a first CoCrPtB alloy;
a sixth layer comprising a second CoCrPtB alloy, wherein said second CoCrPtB alloy is different than said first CoCrPtB alloy;
and a protective overcoat.

9. A system for recording data, comprising;
a circumferentially textured glass substrate;
a first layer comprising cobalt and tungsten deposited directly over said textured glass substrate, said first layer having a tungsten content of 30 to 50 atomic percentage; and
a mutli-layer structure having magnetic properties deposited over said first layer, wherein the first layer has a (002)\(11-20) texture.

11. The system of claim 9 wherein said mutli-layer structure further comprises
a second layer comprising Cr;
a third layer comprising a CrMoTa alloy;
a fourth layer comprising a CoCrTa alloy;
a fifth layer comprising a first CoCrPtB alloy;
a sixth layer comprising a second CoCrPtB alloy, wherein said second CoCrPtB alloy is different than said first CoCrPtB alloy; and
a protective overcoat.
